    "title": "Lead Instructional Designer at British Council India Digital Technologies",
    "description": "British Council India Digital Technologies, one of India's leading organizations, is hiring a Instructional Designer for our Hyderabad operations. We offer a competitive salary package along with world-class benefits.\n\nAbout British Council India Digital Technologies:\nBritish Council India Digital Technologies is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Contribute to school newsletter, blogs, and other publications\n• Monitor student progress and provide timely feedback\n• Conduct parent-teacher meetings and update parents on student performance\n• Design formative and summative assessments aligned to learning objectives\n• Collaborate with faculty on curriculum development initiatives\n• Conduct doubt-clearing sessions and remedial classes for weak students\n• Maintain classroom discipline and create a positive learning environment\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Zoom/Teams\n• Proficiency in Special Education\n• Proficiency in Bloom's Taxonomy\n• Proficiency in Educational Technology\n• Proficiency in Student Assessment\n• Proficiency in Communication Skills\n• Proficiency in Classroom Management\n• Proficiency in Lesson Planning\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Learning & development budget\n• Life and accident insurance\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Hyderabad, Telangana, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with British Council India Digital Technologies!",
